   "source": [
    "9.What are *args and **kwargs?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4651aedc-41bf-4345-b0f3-6f3774c4c451",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*args -> gives output in tuples, its a positional arguments\n",
    "**kwargs -> gives output in dictionary, its a keyword argument\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "ccf0aaec-c0f6-4a95-a5d8-d8a9c086df37",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Positional: (1, 2, 3, 4, 5)\n",
      "Keyword: {'name': 'sam', 'age': 24}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def print_all(*args,**kwargs):\n",
    "    print(\"Positional:\",args)\n",
    "    print(\"Keyword:\",kwargs)\n",
    "print_all(1,2,3,4,5,name=\"sam\",age=24)"
   ]
  }
 ],
